    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so if the main goal is to change behavior, what about the people who literally can't take the bus or train? like people who have to drive for work or live in areas where transit is basically non-existent. isn't it kind of unfair to basically tax them for something they can't avoid? it feels more like punishing the working class than actually helping the planet.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
