      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This is a fundamental equity issue that proponents of congestion pricing are actively addressing through policy design. The solution isn't to scrap the pricing, but to aggressively subsidize or expand transit options in those underserved areas *before* the pricing goes live. If a city fails to provide viable alternatives, then the system is indeed unjust, but the pricing itself is a necessary lever to force that infrastructure investment.",
      "source": "target",
